Usage: gskill add <source> [flags]

Add and install a new skill.

Examples:

    gskill add github.com/owner/repo                # guided wizard on a terminal
    gskill add github.com/owner/repo --agent claude
    gskill add github.com/owner/repo --skill deploy-helper --version '^2.0.0'
    gskill add ./local/skills --all
    gskill add github.com/owner/repo --list
    gskill add github.com/owner/repo --dry-run      # print the plan, write nothing

Arguments:
  <source>    Skill source: git shorthand, URL, or local path.

Flags:
  -h, --help                   Show context-sensitive help.
      --json                   Emit machine-readable JSON on stdout.
      --quiet                  Suppress diagnostics on stderr.
      --no-interactive         Disable prompts and colored output.
      --yes                    Assume yes for confirmation prompts.
      --offline                Operate without network access.
      --no-cache               Bypass the content cache.
      --dry-run                Report actions without applying them.
      --config=STRING          Path to a config file.
  -v, --verbose                Enable verbose diagnostics.
  -C, --dir=STRING             Run as if gskill started in this directory.

      --skill=SKILL,...        Select a discovered skill by name (repeatable;
                               '*' selects all; name@path disambiguates).
      --all                    Select every valid discovered skill.
      --list                   List discovered skills without installing.
      --path=STRING            In-repo path disambiguator for a duplicated
                               --skill.
      --version=STRING         Semver constraint (e.g. ^2.0.0).
      --ref=STRING             Branch or tag to track.
      --commit=STRING          Explicit commit SHA to pin.
      --exact                  Pin to the exact resolved version.
      --agent=AGENT,...        Target agent ID (repeatable). Additive: adds to,
                               never replaces, a skill's already-installed
                               agents. To replace a skill's agent set outright,
                               use 'gskill install --agent'.
      --force                  Overwrite an existing declaration and re-resolve.
      --global                 Install into the user-global location.
      --project                Install into the project (default).
      --auto                   Prefer a symlink, fall back to a copy (default).
      --copy                   Copy instead of linking.
      --symlink                Symlink, never copy.
      --max-depth=INT          Maximum recursive scan depth (0 = unbounded).
      --include=INCLUDE,...    Only discover skills whose in-repo path matches
                               this glob (repeatable).
      --exclude=EXCLUDE,...    Skip skills whose in-repo path matches this glob
                               (repeatable).
